text: Expected Gas Cost (EGC): A component of the GCR, the EGC is the price the local utility expects to pay for natural gas
label: BODY

text: in the upcoming GCR rate period. For example, if the GCR rate is filed on a monthly basis, the local utility will calculate
label: BODY

text: the EGC for the following month. Gas costs recoverable through the EGC include the cost of purchasing the gas itself as
label: BODY

text: Gas Cost Recovery (GCR) Rate: A mechanism that provides a dollar-for-dollar recovery of costs incurred by a local
label: BODY

text: utility to purchase natural gas to its system. The GCR mechanism enables the local utility to correct any over or under
label: BODY

text: GCR Transition (GCRT) Rider: An adjustment used to reimburse or charge customers for any under or over recovery of
label: BODY

label: BODY

text: participation as a CHOICE customer, the GCR transition rider is eliminated from the customer’s bill. Because the GCR
